Adjust rack to middle position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Peel and dice @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch pieces.

Reserve 1 tsp maple syrup for sweet potatoes (2 tsp for 4); pour @maple syrup{2%tbsp} into a #small bowl{}. Stir in a @salt{pinch} and @chili flakes to taste. Set aside.

Place sweet potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender when pierced with a fork, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Drain and return sweet potatoes to #pot{}. Mash off heat with reserved maple syrup, half the @sour cream{2%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later), @butter{1%tbsp}, salt, and @pepper. Cover to keep warm.

== Panko Mixture ==

While sweet potatoes cook, place @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @Fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, @olive oil{1%tbsp}, and a @salt{pinch}.

== Poached Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @salt and @pepper.

Lightly oil a #baking sheet{} with @vegetable oil{1%tsp} and place chicken on one side. (For 4 servings, spread chicken out across entire sheet.) Evenly spread remaining sour cream onto tops of chicken; mound with panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Roast chicken on middle rack for ~{8%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then).

== Roasted Green Beans ==

While chicken roasts, toss @green beans{6%oz} in a #medium bowl{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @salt, and @pepper.

Once chicken has roasted ~{8%minutes}, remove sheet from oven and carefully add green beans to empty side. (For 4 servings, leave chicken roasting and add green beans to a second sheet; roast on top rack.)

Continue roasting until chicken is cooked through and green beans are tender, ~{12-15%minutes} more.

== Assembly ==

Divide sweet potatoes, chicken, and green beans between plates. Drizzle chicken with spicy maple syrup and sprinkle with more chili flakes if desired. Serve.

> Said sauce would also be unbelievable on pancakes.